:'''Abraham:''' P&mdash;Please rest assured that this zone is now completely under the con&mdash;control of the Curio Collection Squad!
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why is your voice shaking?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022233-->
::'''Abraham:''' Shaking? It i&mdash;is not. You must've misheard.
::'''Abraham:''' Phew, phew... Calm down, Abraham. As a member of the Curio Collection Squad, you must always stay calm.
::'''Abraham:''' Fear, if picked up by others, will not only make everyone distrust you, but also ruin your chance to avenge Alfred.
::'''Abraham:''' Mrs. Hinkel transferred me here from the Obstacle Detection Terminal so that I could follow the lead of Wen Mingde, head of the Curio Collection Squad, to toughen myself up on the front line.
::'''Abraham:''' But as soon as I came here, I encountered a problem about, about...
::'''Abraham:''' Reactivating the Space Anchor over there!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That's too hard.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022245-->
:::'''Abraham:''' You think so too!? Great, I'm not alone.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Even I can do it.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022247-->
:::'''Abraham:''' Don't put it like that... You are the big hero who saved the space station. This's not something that anyone can do. You are being too modest...
::'''Abraham:''' Well, actually, the activation itself isn't the difficult part. You just need to get close to the Space Anchor, and the biological polarity of your body will be enough to activate it.
::'''Abraham:''' The real challenge is all the monsters along the way.
::'''Abraham:''' Back when I was working at the Obstacle Detection Terminal, they were nothing but distant shadows that I could just brush aside.
::'''Abraham:''' Then the invasion happened. And when I learned that they got Alfred, my heart began to fill up with hatred.
::'''Abraham:''' But when I became a member of the Curio Collection Squad and met them face to face, all I felt was fear!
::'''Abraham:''' At that moment, Alfred's fading eyes flashed in my head. I felt short of breath, with cold sweat all over my body and my legs trembling...
::'''Abraham:''' What a loser, right? I just couldn't find the courage to go through with it and activate the Space Anchor. And it had been like this for several days...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I remember you. You are that guy who is morbidly scared of death.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022237-->
::'''Abraham:''' Remember me? I&mdash;I also remember you... But now I'm not a&mdash;afraid of death anymore...
::'''Abraham:''' The friends who had once stood by my side day and night have already taken the lead in entering the eternal night, and yet I'm still here, not knowing when my life will end.
::'''Abraham:''' Life is but a path to death, but not today.
::'''Abraham:''' I don't want to die at the hands of those monsters until I avenge Alfred!
::'''Abraham:''' Mrs. Hinkel transferred me here from the Obstacle Detection Terminal so that I could follow the lead of Wen Mingde, head of the Curio Collection Squad, to toughen myself up on the front line.
::'''Abraham:''' But as soon as I came here, I encountered a problem about, about...
::'''Abraham:''' Reactivating the Space Anchor over there!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That's too hard.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022245-->
:::'''Abraham:''' You think so too!? Great, I'm not alone.
:::'''Abraham:''' Well, actually, the activation itself isn't the difficult part. You just need to get close to the Space Anchor, and the biological polarity of your body will be enough to activate it.
:::'''Abraham:''' The real challenge is all the monsters along the way.
:::'''Abraham:''' Back when I was working at the Obstacle Detection Terminal, they were nothing but distant shadows that I could just brush aside.
:::'''Abraham:''' Then the invasion happened. And when I learned that they got Alfred, my heart began to fill up with hatred.
:::'''Abraham:''' But when I became a member of the Curio Collection Squad and met them face to face, all I felt was fear!
:::'''Abraham:''' At that moment, Alfred's fading eyes flashed in my head. I felt short of breath, with cold sweat all over my body and my legs trembling...
:::'''Abraham:''' What a loser, right? I just couldn't find the courage to go through with it and activate the Space Anchor. And it had been like this for several days...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Even I can do it.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022247-->
:::'''Abraham:''' Don't put it like that... You are the big hero who saved the space station. This's not something that anyone can do. You are being too modest...
:::'''Abraham:''' Well, actually, the activation itself isn't the difficult part. You just need to get close to the Space Anchor, and the biological polarity of your body will be enough to activate it.
:::'''Abraham:''' The real challenge is all the monsters along the way.
:::'''Abraham:''' Back when I was working at the Obstacle Detection Terminal, they were nothing but distant shadows that I could just brush aside.
:::'''Abraham:''' Then the invasion happened. And when I learned that they got Alfred, my heart began to fill up with hatred.
:::'''Abraham:''' But when I became a member of the Curio Collection Squad and met them face to face, all I felt was fear!
:::'''Abraham:''' At that moment, Alfred's fading eyes flashed in my head. I felt short of breath, with cold sweat all over my body and my legs trembling...
:::'''Abraham:''' What a loser, right? I just couldn't find the courage to go through with it and activate the Space Anchor. And it had been like this for several days...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The solution is just a few steps away!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022249-->
:::'''Abraham:''' It may look like a few steps, but I can't do it, even if I muster all my courage...
:::'''Abraham:''' Well, actually, the activation itself isn't the difficult part. You just need to get close to the Space Anchor, and the biological polarity of your body will be enough to activate it.
:::'''Abraham:''' The real challenge is all the monsters along the way.
:::'''Abraham:''' Back when I was working at the Obstacle Detection Terminal, they were nothing but distant shadows that I could just brush aside.
:::'''Abraham:''' Then the invasion happened. And when I learned that they got Alfred, my heart began to fill up with hatred.
:::'''Abraham:''' But when I became a member of the Curio Collection Squad and met them face to face, all I felt was fear!
:::'''Abraham:''' At that moment, Alfred's fading eyes flashed in my head. I felt short of breath, with cold sweat all over my body and my legs trembling...
:::'''Abraham:''' What a loser, right? I just couldn't find the courage to go through with it and activate the Space Anchor. And it had been like this for several days...
:::'''Abraham:''' So, (Trailblazer), do you think you can...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Leave it to me!
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022259-->
::'''Abraham:''' I really admire you. Your perserverance and courage in the face of death have inspired me.
::'''Abraham:''' I'm well aware of my limitations, so I'll just wait here for an update from you.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Let's go together. We can look out for each other.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022262-->
::'''Abraham:''' N&mdash;N&mdash;No, I can't. I'll just get in the way...
:'''Abraham:''' (Trailblazer), please {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|activate the Space Anchor}}. I am counting on you!
